  {id:"asl",title:"ASL Letter Recognition",category:"ai-ml",emoji:"🤟",
   image:"assets/img/asl_recognition.gif",
   tagline:"Real-time sign language detection · 90.38% accuracy · PyTorch MLP",
   tags:["PyTorch","MediaPipe","Computer Vision","Flask","Python"],
   metrics:[{v:"90.38%",l:"Validation Accuracy"},{v:"87K+",l:"Training Images"},{v:"63-dim",l:"Feature Vector"}],
   overview:"Real-time ASL letter recognition system for 10 high-frequency letters (A, E, I, L, O, R, S, T, U, Y). MediaPipe extracts 21 hand landmarks per frame, fed into a custom 3-layer PyTorch MLP. Submitted for AAI3001: Computer Vision and Deep Learning.",
   problem:"Standardized Kaggle training images (professional lighting, controlled angles) caused domain adaptation issues with real consumer webcams. Standard classifiers also struggled with ASL class imbalance.",
   solution:"Built an end-to-end pipeline: MediaPipe Hand Landmarker extracts 21 anatomical landmarks (63-dimensional vector) per image, merged with 250 custom webcam samples collected under varied lighting. MLP (256-128-64, ReLU, 30% dropout) trained with Adam, ReduceLROnPlateau scheduler, and early stopping. Deployed via Flask for real-time webcam inference.",
   impact:["90.38% validation accuracy on 10-class ASL recognition","Custom dataset of 250 samples collected across varied real-world conditions improved generalization","Deployed as real-time Flask web app with webcam demo","Submitted for AAI3001 (Computer Vision and Deep Learning)"],
