  {id:"churn",title:"Customer Churn Prediction",category:"ai-ml",emoji:"📊",
   image:"",
   tagline:"XGBoost + SMOTE-ENN · 81.28% recall · 0.8263 AUC · SHAP explainability",
   tags:["XGBoost","SMOTE-ENN","SHAP","Python","Scikit-learn"],
   metrics:[{v:"81.28%",l:"Recall"},{v:"0.8263",l:"AUC"},{v:"62.94%",l:"F1 Score"}],
   overview:"ML pipeline predicting customer churn in subscription-based industries. Compares 8 resampling techniques under identical conditions and uses SHAP for directional, per-customer churn explanations rather than just a probability score. Submitted for AAI2002, currently being extended toward real-time edge deployment on point-of-sale terminals.",
   problem:"Churn prediction is a class imbalance problem (only 26.58% of IBM Telco customers churned, 1:2.76 ratio). A naive classifier predicting everyone as retained still achieves high accuracy. An untuned XGBoost baseline hits only 52.05% recall, leaving nearly half of all churners undetected. Missing a churner forfeits remaining lifetime value and incurs reacquisition costs reported as 5 to 25 times the cost of retention.",
   solution:"Eight resampling techniques were compared. SMOTE-ENN produced the highest recall and cleaned noisy boundary samples. Dual GridSearchCV runs (scoring=f1 and scoring=recall) were run; the recall-tuned model (lr=0.01, depth=3, n=100, threshold=0.50) was selected. SHAP was chosen over XGBoost built-in importance and LIME for its directional per-customer waterfall explanations.",
   impact:["81.28% recall vs 52.05% untuned baseline (56% improvement)","0.8263 AUC, 62.94% F1 on held-out test set","Contract type identified as strongest churn driver (mean SHAP 0.7143): month-to-month customers significantly more likely to churn","Tenure and absence of online security/tech support ranked second and third globally","Being extended toward real-time edge deployment on POS terminals"],
   tech:["XGBoost","SMOTE-ENN","SHAP","Pandas","Scikit-learn","Matplotlib","Google Colab"],
   github:"https://github.com/mlemxy/churn-prediction",demo:"https://colab.research.google.com/github/mlemxy/churn-prediction/blob/main/main.ipynb"},

